**Token-level outcomes:**

| Status | Token class | Outcome | Corrupted → Predicted | Gold |
|:---:|---|---|---|---|
| ✓ | IN_CLASS | TP | `stduy` → `study` | `study` |
| ✗ | IN_CLASS | FN_missed | `deascribed` → `deascribed` | `described` |
| ✓ | IN_CLASS | TP | `infkammatory` → `inflammatory` | `inflammatory` |
| ✓ | IN_CLASS | TP | `stble` → `stable` | `stable` |
| ✓ | IN_CLASS | TP | `appearanec` → `appearance` | `appearance` |
| ✓ | IN_CLASS | TP | `oeritoneal` → `peritoneal` | `peritoneal` |
| ✓ | IN_CLASS | TP | `blooe` → `blood` | `blood` |

The missed correction (`deascribed`) illustrates a known limitation: insertions
at the start of a word (`de-` prefix) can be difficult to distinguish from valid
morphological variants, and the model chose not to alter the token. Lab values,
timestamps, and numeric strings (`wbc-3.9*`, `11: 28am`, `hco3-16*`) were
correctly left untouched throughout.